-- Premier Berlusconi Sees $100 Billion of Trade With China Within 5 Years
-- B y   J e f f r e y   D o n o v a n
-- 2010-10-07T11:24:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/premier-berlusconi-sees-100-billion-of-trade-with-china-within-5-years.html
Italian Prime Minister Silvio
Berlusconi said he and Chinese Premier Wen Jiabao agreed to
increase trade between their countries to $100 billion within
five years.  Berlusconi was speaking today at a joint press conference
with Wen in Rome.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeffrey Donovan at 
 jdonovan26@bloomberg.net  